title: The Secret Life of Cats - [National Geographic] Documentary
description: Traditionally, historians tended to think Ancient Egypt was the site of cat domestication. However, in 2004, a Neolithic grave excavated in Cyprus contained the skeletons, laid close to one another, of both a human and a cat. The grave is estimated to be 9,500 years old, pushing back the earliest known felineâ€“human association significantly. The cat specimen is large and closely resembles the African wildcat, rather than present-day domestic cats.

title: Follow Your Cat - What Felines get up to When They Leave the House | Free Documentary Nature
description: Do you know your cat? When she is not purring on your living room sofa - do you know where she roams? Do you know where she wanders off once she leaves the premises? No? Well, would you like to? Follow us while we follow cats on their hunting grounds for mice and birds. Experience the double life of your domestic tiger... She will lead you on adventures that you never thought were possible. With a behavioural scientist that specializes in cats and modern technology we follow the cat on their wanderings into the wild. She maps their routes, unveils their secret favourite places, chronicles their territorial conquests, and shows us the entertaining habits of this enigmatic creature.
